This paper is about fine-grained recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision. The proposed method uses reinforcement learning to adaptively select multiple visual attention regions, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks, which is a popular technique in deep learning and falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of attention mechanisms, which is a topic in both machine learning and natural language processing, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The use of reinforcement learning also falls under the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
